[assistant] Fixed the failing `JaninoCompilerTest`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - `JaninoCompiler.compile()` requires `args.destdir` to be non-null.
[assistant] - The generated class was also package-scoped, which would require package directories when Janino writes `.class` files.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changes:
[assistant] - Added a JUnit `@TempDir` output directory.
[assistant] - Set `args.setDestdir(outputDirectory.toString())`.
[assistant] - Switched the generated test source to the default package so Janino can write the class file directly under the temp directory.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated commit:
[assistant] - `0de9972d0b Add Calcite JaninoCompiler coverage test`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not rerun the Gradle test locally.
[assistant-event] text_end
